<dl id="n28049c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n28" href="#n28049c">N28 (VI.D.6)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n28all.htm#n28049c"> 49(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Lambert Simnell <font face="wake">C</font> carried on shoulder of big d&apos;Arcy of Platten</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[The Story of Dublin]</font> <font color="green">[History lovers]</font> may also recall how little <mark>Lambert Simnell was carried on the shoulders of big D&apos;Arcy of Platten</mark> from the Castle to be crowned at Christ Church Cathedral as Edward VI., and the child imposter wore a crown taken from a statue of Mary le Dam. <small> A. Peter, <a name="APDF1" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#APDF1"><cite title="source">Dublin Fragments, social and historic</cite></a> (1925) 10</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
